font-size:18.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=p  style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:14.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" >The development of the Digital Mobile Store system was carried out locally within a unified development environment (such as XAMPP). Upon completion, the project is structured to be deployed seamlessly onto any standard Linux-based production web server or cloud hosting provider that supports modern PHP and MySQL environments.</span><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:12.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></p><h1 style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;color:rgb(0,0,0);
font-weight:bold;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:24.0000pt;
mso-font-kerning:22.0000pt;" ><font face="SimSun" >Chapter-2: Requirement Analysis</font></span></b><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;font-weight:bold;
text-transform:uppercase;font-size:24.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:22.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></b></h1><h2 style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;color:rgb(0,0,0);
font-weight:bold;font-size:18.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><font face="SimSun" >2.1 Introduction</font></span></b><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;font-weight:bold;
font-size:18.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=p  style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:14.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" >Requirement analysis is a fundamental phase in the software development life cycle of the phoneKART system. It entails understanding the exact needs of the stakeholders—both the store owners (administrators) and the online shoppers (customers). This phase ensures that the final product directly addresses the limitations of the physical store while providing a robust, error-free online shopping experience.</span><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:12.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;color:rgb(0,0,0);
font-weight:bold;font-size:18.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><font face="SimSun" >2.2 Tools Used for Requirement Gathering</font></span></b><b><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:SimSun;font-weight:bold;
font-size:18.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=p  style="mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;" ><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:14.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" >To ensure a comprehensive understanding of the project requirements, several fact-finding techniques were employed:</span><span style="mso-spacerun:'yes';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:12.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;" ><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal  align=justify  style="margin-top:5.0000pt;margin-bottom:4.8000pt;margin-left:12.0000pt;
